During a visit to Malibu, California, President Trump expressed his condolences to those affected by the wildfires and praised the government officials for their response. He also discussed the need for expedited rebuilding and the importance of collaboration and cooperation between the federal government and the state of California. The President mentioned the need for improved land and forest management to prevent future wildfires. He also addressed the issue of climate change, stating that all factors will be considered in finding solutions to the problem. The President assured that funding will be provided to support the recovery efforts and mentioned that a report on the assassination of journalist Jamal Khashoggi will be released soon. He concluded by expressing his commitment to supporting the shooting victims and their families.